{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:37:39.915Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Versioning experiments"},{"type":"text","text":" is the practice of treating ML experiments as immutable, versioned artifacts—by snapshotting the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"codebase state, data version, hyperparameters, pipeline configuration, and resulting metrics"},{"type":"text","text":" for each experiment run—so you can reproduce, compare, and restore any past experiment at any time, rather than just logging metrics in a dashboard."}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key difference:"},{"type":"text","text":" Tracking experiments = logging metrics, parameters, and artifacts in a dashboard. Versioning experiments = codifying experiments as code so logs are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"always connected to the exact data, code, and pipeline that produced them"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What experiment versioning is (conceptually)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Experiment versioning brings together:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Code versioning"},{"type":"text","text":" (Git commits)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Data versioning"},{"type":"text","text":" (DVC or similar)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pipeline versioning"},{"type":"text","text":" (DVC pipeline config)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parameter and metrics versioning"},{"type":"text","text":" (text files like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"params.yaml"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"metrics.json"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This creates a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single atomic record"},{"type":"text","text":" for each experiment that captures everything needed to reproduce it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core idea:"},{"type":"text","text":" “Experiment versioning treats experiments as code. It saves all metrics, hyperparameters, and artifact information in text files that can be versioned.” "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://dvc.org/blog/ml-experiment-versioning/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"dvc"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why versioning matters (vs. just tracking)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem with tracking-only approaches"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you only "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"track experiments"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., with a dashboard):"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You log metrics, parameters, Git commit, etc."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"But to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reproduce"},{"type":"text","text":" a result later, you must:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Manually trace back to the exact code commit - Manually restore the exact data version - Manually reconstruct the pipeline"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tracking alone doesn’t guarantee you can "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"restore"},{"type":"text","text":" the experiment easily."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How versioning solves this"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Experiment versioning:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Connects experiment logs to exact data, code, and pipeline"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reproduce or restore"},{"type":"text","text":" an experiment with a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single command"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Enables:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reproducibility"},{"type":"text","text":": Run the same experiment again with the same setup - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Comparison"},{"type":"text","text":": See how metrics changed across iterations - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Iteration"},{"type":"text","text":": Start from a previous experiment and make "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"only the necessary changes"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Versioned reproducibility means tracking changes to the experiment state. DVC can determine what changes were introduced by the experiment and only run what’s necessary.”"}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text